topics.body:
"@twistedmetalero":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/535aa3446368726f15890100#post_535aa3446368726f15890100
Did you try turning it off and on again? :V

But in all seriousness here's a quick way to diagnose what's wrong with your computer; if when you try turning it on you hear a beeping sound that's something hardware wise failed, if you turn it on and it's a blank screen that's a corrupted bios(just look up your computer version, google bios and then the computer version and follow the steps; normally it's pretty easy steps of just slapping it on a thumbdrive, press a couple buttons and presto fixed).  If it's neither of these it's either the power supply or I don't know.

Oh also if it's a series of beeps instead of a singular beep or a long beep that's normally a ram stick gave out.  Normally in this case it's a series of four beeps(normally), if that's the case take out all the ram sticks then insert them one by one until you figured out which one is broken.
